'''Lucas Erik Holger Bergvall''' ({{IPA|sv|ˈlu:kɑs bæ̌ɾj:vɑl|lang|}}; born 2 February 2006) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

== Club career ==
=== IF Brommapojkarna ===
Born and raised in [[Stockholm]], Bergvall advanced through the academy of [[IF Brommapojkarna]], where he was part of the winning team of the 2019 U13 Madrid Football Cup, beating youth teams from the academies of [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|Bayern Munich]], [[Atlético Madrid]], [[Paris Saint-Germain FC Youth Academy|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[La Masia|Barcelona]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Lucas Bergvall: Tottenham's new teenage wonderkid who turned down Barcelona to join Ange Postecoglou's revolution |url=https://www.goal.com/lists/lucas-bergvall-tottenham-teenage-wonderkid-turned-down-barcelona/bltcb6b88d0ce0e832a#csa346f8d574fe7d65|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=2 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Storartad seger i Madrid Football Cup för P06-1 – BP|date=16 September 2019|publisher=IF Brommapojkarna|url=https://bpfotboll.se/forening/storartad-seger-i-madrid-football-cup-for-p06-1/|access-date=18 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Madrid Football Cup players in the most important leagues - Madrid Football Agency|date=18 July 2022|publisher=Madrid Football Agency|url=https://www.madridfootballagency.com/madrid-football-cup-players-in-the-most-important-leagues/|access-date=18 September 2025}}</ref> Bergvall made his [[Superettan]] debut for Brommapojkarna on 9 July 2022 in a 1–1 draw with [[Örgryte IS|Örgryte]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/07/19/sweden/superettan/orgryte-ildrottssalskap/ildrottsforening--brommapojkarna/3731227/ |title=Örgryte vs. Brommapojkarna |website=Soccerway |date=19 July 2022}}</ref> On 4 October 2022, he scored his first professional goal against [[Östers IF|Öster]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/10/04/sweden/superettan/osters-ildrottsforening/ildrottsforening--brommapojkarna/3731320/ |title=Öster vs. Brommapojkarna |website=Soccerway |date=4 October 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://fotbolldirekt.se/2022/10/05/lucas-bergvall-slog-till-med-sitt-forsta-mal-i-superettan |title=Lucas Bergvall slog till med sitt första mål i superettan |website=Fotbolldirekt |date=5 October 2022 |language=sv}}</ref> Heavily scouted in his youth, Bergvall participated in trials at [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] during his time at Brommapojkarna.<ref>{{cite web|first=Alasdiar|last=Gold|title=Lucas Bergvall - Inside his move to Tottenham, why he rejected Barcelona and Son's welcome text|date=6 February 2024|publisher=football.london|url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/transfer-news/lucas-bergvall-tottenhams-frenkie-de-28580263|access-date=18 September 2025}}</ref>

=== Djurgården ===
Bergvall joined [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgården]] on 9 December 2022 and made his debut as a starter for the team in [[Allsvenskan]] in the game against champions [[BK Häcken|Häcken]] on 24 May 2023. After a strong contribution in Djurgården's 1–0 victory, Swedish newspaper ''[[Aftonbladet]]'' described Bergvall as the man of the match and forecast that he would become "Djurgården's biggest transfer ever".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/8JWXO1/lucas-bergvall-i-startelvan-for-att-stanna|url-access=subscription|first=Daniel|last=Kristoffersson|title=Lucas Bergvall i startelvan för att stanna|newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]]|date=24 May 2023|language=sv}}</ref> On 11 October 2023, he was named by English newspaper ''[[The Guardian]]'' as one of the best players born in 2006 worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|title=Next Generation 2023: 60 of the best young talents in world football|first1=Marcus|last1=Christenson|first2=Steven|last2=Bloor|first3=Garry|last3=Blight|newspaper=The Guardian|date=11 October 2023|access-date=6 May 2025}}</ref> Bergvall made 37 league appearances in total, scoring five goals and providing two assists.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Profile|url=https://nr.soccerway.com/players/lucas-bergvall/805559/|website=Soccerway|access-date=2 September 2024}}</ref>

=== Tottenham Hotspur ===
'''2024–25: Debut and Player of the Season'''

On 2 February 2024, [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] agreed a five-year deal to sign Bergvall for a reported transfer fee of £8.5&nbsp;million, competing with [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] for his signature. He officially joined the club on 1 July 2024.<ref>{{Cite news|first=BBC|last=Sport|title=Lucas Bergvall: Tottenham agree deal for 18-year-old Swedish midfielder |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68188921|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=2 February 2024|access-date=4 October 2025}}</ref> On 17 July 2024, he made his first Spurs appearance as a half-time substitute in a 5–1 pre-season [[Friendly (football)|friendly]] victory against [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]]; in the 66th minute he assisted [[Mikey Moore]] to put Tottenham up 3–1.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jenkins |first=Seb |date=17 April 2024|title=Tottenham second-half player ratings: 5–1 pre-season win over Hearts |url=https://www.spurs-web.com/news/tottenham-second-half-player-ratings-5-1-pre-season-win-over-hearts/ |access-date=20 July 2024|website=The Spurs Web}}</ref> On 20 July 2024, Bergvall was granted a spot in the Starting XI for a friendly match against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]; in the 24th minute he went down with an undisclosed injury.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Horn |first=Kieran |date=20 July 2024|title=Tottenham suffer major Bergvall injury blow in pre-season friendly |url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/news/breaking-tottenham-suffer-major-injury-29580998 |access-date=5 May 2025|website=Football London}}</ref>

Bergvall's first start for the club came in a 2–1 [[2024–25 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] victory against [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on 18 September 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 September 2024|first=Joe|last=Rindl|title=Coventry 1–2 Tottenham: Win papers over performance|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c749x977veko|website=BBC Sport|access-date=19 September 2024}}</ref> On 8 January 2025, he scored his first goal for Tottenham in a 1–0 win against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the first leg of the EFL Cup semi-final.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Michael|last=Jones|title=Tottenham vs Liverpool LIVE: Carabao Cup score and updates as Porro misses great chance after Bentancur injury|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-liverpool-carabao-cup-live-stream-score-result-b2674462.html|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=8 January 2025|access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref>

On 29 April 2025, Bergvall signed a new contract with Tottenham, which is set to expire in 2031.<ref>{{cite web |title=New deal for Bergvall|date=29 April 2025 |website=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/april/new-deal-for-bergvall/ |access-date=29 April 2025}}</ref> On 1 May, Bergvall suffered an ankle injury during training, having to use crutches while attending Tottenham's 3–1 [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] semi-final first leg victory against [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Team News – Ange on Bergvall Absence|website=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=1 May 2025|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/may/team-news-ange-postecoglou-on-lucas-bergvall-absence/|access-date=2 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Guest|first=Rob|title=Lucas Bergvall on crutches and double Tottenham injury concern for Ange Postecoglou vs Bodo/Glimt|date=1 May 2025|website=Football London|url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/fixtures-results/lucas-bergvall-crutches-double-tottenham-31554168?int_source=mantis_rec&int_medium=web&int_campaign=more_like_this|access-date=2 May 2025}}</ref> Head coach [[Ange Postecoglou]] revealed that Bergvall had sustained damage to the ligaments in his ankle and would miss the remainder of [[2024–25 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Update {{!}} Lucas Bergvall|website=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=2 May 2025|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/may/update-lucas-bergvall/|access-date=2 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ange Postecoglou on Lucas Bergvall: "I've no doubt he'll come back stronger"|website=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=2 May 2025|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/may/ange-postecoglou-on-lucas-bergvall-ive-no-doubt-hell-come-back-stronger/|access-date=2 May 2025}}</ref> On 15 May, Bergvall was voted as Tottenham Official Supporters' Club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.#Player of the Year|Player of the Season]], as well as One Hotspur Members and One Hotspur Juniors Player of the Season for the [[2024–25 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2024–25]] season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bergvall completes Player of the Season clean sweep|date=15 May 2025|website=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/may/bergvall-completes-player-of-the-season-clean-sweep/|access-date=15 May 2025}}</ref>

'''2025–26 season'''

On 13 September 2025, Bergvall scored his first Premier League goal for Tottenham in a 3–0 win away against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], and was awarded Player of the Match. He became the second-youngest Tottenham player to score and assist in a Premier League game.<ref>{{cite web |title=West Ham vs Tottenham Hotspur: Lucas Bergvall scores his first Premier League goal|date=13 September 2025 |website=Sky Sports |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/video/12606/13430450/goal-l-bergvall-57-west-ham-0-2-tottenham-hotspur |access-date=13 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lucas Bergvall becomes second-youngest Spurs player ever to score and assist in a Premier League game after starring role in thumping of West Ham |website=Yahoo Sports |url=https://au.sports.yahoo.com/lucas-bergvall-becomes-second-youngest-192539995.html |access-date=14 September 2025}}</ref> On 16 September, Bergvall made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in a 1–0 home victory against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]], creating the chance that led to Villarreal goalkeeper [[Luiz Júnior (footballer, born 2001)|Luiz Júnior]] fumbling the ball into his own net, resulting in the only goal of the match. He was subsequently awarded Player of the Match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tottenham 1-0 Villarreal: Luiz Junior own goal seals win for Spurs - BBC Sport|date=16 September 2025|publisher=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn76vydrlrmt|access-date=17 September 2025}}</ref> On 1 November, Bergvall suffered a concussion early in a 1–0 loss to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], keeping him out of action for a few weeks in compliance with the FA's 'Graduated return to play' (GRTP) programme.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tottenham Hotspur 0-1 Chelsea: Joao Pedro scores winner as hosts booed off|date=1 November 2025|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3dn1j7nn4zt#Line-ups|access-date=3 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Stokes|first=Jake|title=Bergvall timeline, Solanke update, Gray latest - Tottenham injury news and return dates|date=3 November 2025|publisher=Football.London|url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/news/tottenham-injury-news-bergvall-solanke-32798032|access-date=3 November 2025}}</ref>

== International career ==
Bergvall has represented Sweden at various youth levels, ranging from under-15 until [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]].<ref name="Breaking The Lines">{{Cite web|title=Lucas Bergvall: The Highly Coveted Swedish Prospect Headed for Tottenham Hotspur|url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/lucas-bergvall-the-highly-coveted-swedish-prospect-headed-for-tottenham-hotspur/|website=Breaking The Lines|date=5 February 2024|access-date=7 May 2025}}</ref> On 12 January 2024, he made his [[Sweden men's national football team|senior]] debut as a second-half substitute in a 2–1 friendly victory against [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]].<ref name="Breaking The Lines"/>

On 12 May 2026, Bergvall was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Bergvall comes from a football-centric family.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Harris |first=Jay |title=Lucas Bergvall's road to Tottenham: 'My gut feeling was always Spurs'|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5511680/2024/05/23/lucas-bergvall-tottenham-djurgardens-sweden/|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|via=[[The Athletic]]|date=23 May 2024|access-date=26 October 2024|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Both his older brother, [[Theo Bergvall|Theo]],<ref>{{Cite web|first=Albin|last=Ekström|title=Bröderna Bergvall klara för Djurgården |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/mQMQBg/djurgardens-if-varvar-theo-bergvall-fran-bp-allsvenskan |access-date=22 February 2023 |website=Aftonbladet |date=9 December 2022 |language=sv}}</ref> and his younger brother, Rasmus, are professional footballers.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Makoto|last=Asahara|date=31 May 2024|title=Tredje Bergvall-brorsan i lång intervju: "Vill gå min egen väg" |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/XjgVjm/bp-talangen-rasmus-bergvall-i-lang-intervju-med-sportbladet|newspaper=Aftonbladet|access-date=28 October 2024|language=sv}}</ref>

Growing up, Bergvall supported [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and participated in two trials with the club in 2020 and 2022 respectively.<ref>{{cite news | title=Uppgifter: Manchester United "väldigt intresserat" av Bergvall | trans-title=Reports: Manchester United "very interested" in Bergvall | work=Fotbollskanalen | date=18 January 2024 | url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/artiklar/allsvenskan/uppgifter-manchester-united-valdigt-intresserat-av-bergvall | access-date=23 March 2026 | language=sv | quote=Enligt rapporten är Bergvall dessutom en supporter av Manchester-klubben. [According to the report, Bergvall is also a supporter of the Manchester club.]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Lucas Bergvall was blocked from signing for Man Utd after two trials because of little-known rule | work=SportBible | date=9 January 2025 | url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/football-news/man-utd/lucas-bergvall-tottenham-hotspur-carabao-cup-462535-20250109 | access-date=23 March 2026}}</ref>

